gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 118, Grizzlies 103
gameRecap.excerpt: The Timberwolves defeated the Grizzlies, 118-103. Anthony Edwards recorded 28 points (26 in the second half) along with five rebounds and five assists for the Timberwolves, with Rudy Gobert adding 17 points, 10 rebounds, and six blocks in the victory. Jaren Jackson Jr. tallied 36 points and three rebounds for the Grizzlies in the losing effort. The Timberwolves have won four straight games and improve to 30-11, while the Grizzlies fall to 15-26.
